body:
In this code ([Playground](https://play.rust-lang.org/?version=stable&mode=debug&edition=2018&gist=a60f0298cad004f66c67cdba3ef12f86))
```rust
use futures::executor::block_on;
use futures::future::Future;

fn get_age((age, _): (u8, &&str)) -> impl Future<Output = u8> {
    async move { age }
}

async fn get_age_async((age, _): (u8, &&str)) -> u8 {
    age
}

fn main() {
    block_on(async {
        let _ages = vec![(8, "works")]
            .iter()
            .map(|(value, str)| get_age((*value, &str)))
            .collect::<Vec<_>>();
        let _ages = vec![(8, "doesn't work")]
            .iter()
            .map(|(value, str)| get_age_async((*value, &str)))
            .collect::<Vec<_>>();
    });
}
```
function defined as `fn() -> impl Future` works fine while `async fn` produces error because of its unused argument.
```
error[E0716]: temporary value dropped while borrowed
  --> src/main.rs:18:21
   |
18 |         let _ages = vec![(8, "doesn't work")]
   |                     ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^ creates a temporary which is freed while still in use
...
21 |             .collect::<Vec<_>>();
   |                                 - temporary value is freed at the end of this statement
22 |     });
   |     - borrow might be used here, when `_ages` is dropped and runs the `Drop` code for type `std::vec::Vec`
   |
   = note: consider using a `let` binding to create a longer lived value
   = note: this error originates in a macro outside of the current crate (in Nightly builds, run with -Z external-macro-backtrace for more info)
```
